00:51:55,744 --> 00:51:59,614
Did you find him yet?
Miriam?

517
00:52:21,203 --> 00:52:23,271
Stand back!

518
00:52:49,431 --> 00:52:52,667
[growls]

519
00:52:53,736 --> 00:52:55,904
[gunshot]

520
00:53:02,945 --> 00:53:05,647
Come on, sweetie.

521
00:53:09,185 --> 00:53:10,318
You killed the bad guys?

522
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:12,420
Yeah. You and your rabbit
are safe.

523
00:53:12,422 --> 00:53:15,256
His name is Mr. Bunny.

524
00:53:15,591 --> 00:53:19,227
So why are you out here
all alone?

525
00:53:19,229 --> 00:53:20,361
Where's your mom?

526
00:53:20,363 --> 00:53:22,263
I lost her on the way
to the bunker.

527
00:53:22,265 --> 00:53:23,765
Hey, don't cry.
Listen to me.

528
00:53:23,767 --> 00:53:26,868
I'm gonna get you back
to your mom, okay?

529
00:53:26,870 --> 00:53:29,704
I promise.

530
00:53:29,706 --> 00:53:31,573
Let's go.

531
00:53:45,821 --> 00:53:48,223
[horn honks]

532
00:54:02,805 --> 00:54:03,938
Soldier, open the barrier!

533
00:54:03,940 --> 00:54:06,274
- Sorry, sir, we can't.
- Do you know who I am?

534
00:54:06,276 --> 00:54:09,510
Yes, Colonel Borov, but we
have strict orders not to.

535
00:54:09,512 --> 00:54:11,746
I'm the one who issued
that order!

536
00:54:11,748 --> 00:54:14,649
- Let me through, soldier!
- Yes, sir!

537
00:54:14,651 --> 00:54:18,319
Please! Take my baby!
Save him!

538
00:54:18,321 --> 00:54:21,456
Get back! Get back!

539
00:54:55,924 --> 00:55:00,962
So is this what Captain McGahey
talked to you about?

540
00:55:01,463 --> 00:55:01,963
Yeah.

541
00:55:01,965 --> 00:55:03,298
And what did he tell you?

542
00:55:03,300 --> 00:55:06,334
He said that there were
some unstable weapons

543
00:55:06,336 --> 00:55:07,335
in the warehouses.

544
00:55:07,337 --> 00:55:11,906
He was investigating it.
He didn't tell me much.

545
00:55:15,544 --> 00:55:18,579
Go straight down,
turn right!

546
00:55:18,947 --> 00:55:22,317
They're not dying!

547
00:55:33,362 --> 00:55:34,829
Boss! Boss!

548
00:55:34,831 --> 00:55:37,532
Take it easy, you sluts!

549
00:55:38,467 --> 00:55:41,402
Who did this?

550
00:55:44,707 --> 00:55:46,507
Anton, this is Italian leather!

551
00:55:46,509 --> 00:55:48,976
Bring her to the bathroom,
clean her up!

552
00:55:48,978 --> 00:55:53,381
I will take care of this punk!

553
00:55:53,482 --> 00:55:56,617
Nobody touches my girls!

554
00:55:57,086 --> 00:55:59,620
Ohh...

555
00:56:34,957 --> 00:56:37,525
[screams]

556
00:56:46,034 --> 00:56:48,936
Fucking kook!

557
00:56:53,008 --> 00:56:57,011
Man, I just saw
the most fucked-up thing!

558
00:57:01,950 --> 00:57:04,919
She's dead.

559
00:57:07,022 --> 00:57:09,157
[knocking]

560
00:57:11,627 --> 00:57:13,528
[knocking]

561
00:57:13,530 --> 00:57:17,999
I thought you said
she was dead.

562
00:57:24,840 --> 00:57:28,009
[growling]

563
00:58:08,016 --> 00:58:12,253
[dialing]

564
00:58:12,255 --> 00:58:14,956
[line ringing]

565
00:58:15,958 --> 00:58:19,060
Borov, what the hell
is going on?

566
00:58:19,062 --> 00:58:20,695
<i>[indistinct dialogue]</i>

567
00:58:20,697 --> 00:58:23,731
I just had craziest thing
ever happened.

568
00:58:23,733 --> 00:58:27,201
The whole town
is going to shit!

569
00:58:28,136 --> 00:58:30,238
Mainland? Why?

570
00:58:30,839 --> 00:58:34,909
Code red?
Borov, why didn't you tell me?

571
00:58:34,911 --> 00:58:37,578
What is code red?

572
00:58:50,893 --> 00:58:52,960
[screaming]

573
00:59:22,090 --> 00:59:23,291
Miriam?

574
00:59:23,293 --> 00:59:24,926
Baby?

575
00:59:24,928 --> 00:59:27,562
Sweetheart?

576
00:59:32,200 --> 00:59:34,001
She's been here.

577
00:59:34,003 --> 00:59:36,871
We gotta leave now.

578
00:59:36,873 --> 00:59:40,207
No. We have to look around.

579
00:59:40,209 --> 00:59:44,312
Those footprints,
they're not hers.

580
00:59:44,314 --> 00:59:48,115
[fire crackling]

581
00:59:53,288 --> 00:59:54,956
What are those?

582
00:59:54,958 --> 00:59:56,657
Those are my dog tags.

583
00:59:56,659 --> 00:59:58,759
[chuckles]
You're not a dog.

584
00:59:58,761 --> 01:00:02,663
Soldiers wear these, too.
These were my dad's.

585
01:00:02,665 --> 01:00:05,099
- This is my school.
- Oh, yeah?

586
01:00:05,101 --> 01:00:06,801
Do you have any kids?

587
01:00:06,803 --> 01:00:09,270
A little girl just like you.

588
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:11,172
What's her name?

589
01:00:11,174 --> 01:00:12,974
Olivia.

590
01:00:12,976 --> 01:00:14,709
Where is she?

591
01:00:14,711 --> 01:00:17,178
She's in heaven right now
with her mommy.

592
01:00:17,180 --> 01:00:20,047
- [screeching]
- Get down!

593
01:01:13,301 --> 01:01:16,003
Miss Sarac?

594
01:01:17,139 --> 01:01:19,707
Miss Sarac?

595
01:01:39,795 --> 01:01:41,462
[screaming]

596
01:02:08,890 --> 01:02:12,059
- [whimpering]
- Hey, Miriam, Miriam.

597
01:02:12,061 --> 01:02:15,362
Come here to me.
It's okay, sweetie. Come on.

598
01:02:15,364 --> 01:02:17,865
Come here. Okay.

599
01:02:17,867 --> 01:02:22,002
- [sobbing]
- Shh...

600
01:02:22,004 --> 01:02:23,738
Oh, I got you.

601
01:02:23,740 --> 01:02:29,009
I got you. You're okay.
They're gone, they're gone.

602
01:02:30,812 --> 01:02:35,082
Hey, look who I got.
Mr. Bunny.

603
01:02:35,084 --> 01:02:37,518
Here you go, baby.

604
01:02:39,955 --> 01:02:41,789
Let's go.

605
01:02:54,369 --> 01:02:57,438
- Look!
- Hey!

606
01:02:59,241 --> 01:03:00,875
We're saved!

607
01:03:00,877 --> 01:03:03,477
- Hey!
- No! Villi! Dimo! Stop!

608
01:03:03,479 --> 01:03:05,546
[gunfire]

609
01:03:05,548 --> 01:03:07,481
No!

610
01:03:09,351 --> 01:03:10,384
Get in! Get in!

611
01:03:10,386 --> 01:03:12,419
It's a code red.

612
01:04:41,309 --> 01:04:47,047
[gunfire]

613
01:05:24,286 --> 01:05:26,520
Miriam, come on.

614
01:05:30,058 --> 01:05:32,126
Up here.

615
01:05:38,934 --> 01:05:42,269
Here. Get down.
Get down.

616
01:05:48,476 --> 01:05:51,145
Down, down, down.

617
01:06:02,958 --> 01:06:06,694
They cremating people?

618
01:06:06,696 --> 01:06:09,129
No, sweetie.

619
01:06:09,131 --> 01:06:11,065
Down, down.

620
01:06:11,067 --> 01:06:15,002
I think they're staring
to move away.

621
01:06:15,337 --> 01:06:17,571
It's okay.

622
01:06:22,610 --> 01:06:25,045
Miriam...

623
01:06:25,047 --> 01:06:27,114
Don't cry, okay?

624
01:06:27,116 --> 01:06:30,084
All right?

625
01:06:31,052 --> 01:06:33,620
How's Mr. Bunny doing?

626
01:06:33,622 --> 01:06:37,224
Is he doing all right?
Is he scared?

627
01:06:37,226 --> 01:06:38,592
A bit.

628
01:06:38,594 --> 01:06:41,662
You'll see your mommy soon.

629
01:06:41,664 --> 01:06:43,030
Okay?

630
01:06:43,032 --> 01:06:47,101
Smile. It's okay.

631
01:06:49,004 --> 01:06:50,437
We're pretty close
to the bunker.

632
01:06:50,439 --> 01:06:54,241
You can rest when you see
your mommy. How about that?

633
01:06:54,243 --> 01:06:57,277
Five more minutes?

634
01:07:01,416 --> 01:07:03,117
John?

635
01:07:03,119 --> 01:07:04,184
Yeah?

636
01:07:04,186 --> 01:07:05,185
I'm hungry.

637
01:07:05,187 --> 01:07:07,688
All right, sweetie.
Let's get you some grub.

638
01:07:07,690 --> 01:07:11,392
- Eww.
- [chuckles]

639
01:07:12,160 --> 01:07:15,062
[banging]

640
01:07:15,064 --> 01:07:17,531
Miriam... hang on!

641
01:07:29,344 --> 01:07:30,477
Freeze! On your knees!

642
01:07:30,479 --> 01:07:32,513
- There's infected coming!
- [gunfire]

643
01:07:32,515 --> 01:07:34,314
On your knees or we'll shoot!

644
01:07:34,316 --> 01:07:37,751
I said there's infected coming!

645
01:07:37,753 --> 01:07:41,155
Come on! Get down!

646
01:08:26,701 --> 01:08:28,335
We're clean. Let us in.

647
01:08:28,337 --> 01:08:29,870
We're not allowed
to take anyone.

648
01:08:29,872 --> 01:08:31,238
Come on.
You know you can do it.

649
01:08:31,240 --> 01:08:34,541
We can't take anyone alive.

650
01:08:36,711 --> 01:08:38,745
- At least take the child.
- No!

651
01:08:38,747 --> 01:08:42,416
Miriam, it's okay.
Look, you'll be safe with them.

652
01:08:42,418 --> 01:08:45,652
No! I wanna stay with you.
Please!

653
01:08:45,654 --> 01:08:50,524
A code red is in effect.
We're giving you a privilege.

654
01:08:50,526 --> 01:08:52,693
A privilege? Take the girl.

655
01:08:52,695 --> 01:08:55,629
A privilege
that won't last long.

656
01:08:55,631 --> 01:08:59,333
Move along while you
still have the chance.

657
01:09:01,669 --> 01:09:03,770
Come on, Miriam.

658
01:09:11,279 --> 01:09:13,347
It's okay.

659
01:09:34,369 --> 01:09:37,437
[engine failing]

660
01:09:37,439 --> 01:09:39,473
Shit.

661
01:09:42,243 --> 01:09:44,311
[sighs]

662
01:09:45,313 --> 01:09:47,614
Ana, that's it.

663
01:09:47,616 --> 01:09:49,516
We have to head
to the bridge now.

664
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:52,352
- We've got to keep on going.
- Ana, I'm sorry!

665
01:09:52,354 --> 01:09:54,188
The chances
of a small child surviving

666
01:09:54,190 --> 01:09:57,724
in these circumstances
for this long are not good.

667
01:09:57,726 --> 01:10:02,296
If she's out there,
I'm gonna find her.

668
01:10:02,298 --> 01:10:04,298
Where--

669
01:10:05,867 --> 01:10:09,336
Where are you going?
Where are you gonna go?

670
01:10:09,338 --> 01:10:10,837
I don't know!

671
01:10:10,839 --> 01:10:13,907
- Stop!
- Get off me!

672
01:10:13,909 --> 01:10:14,975
Listen to me!

673
01:10:14,977 --> 01:10:17,344
Miriam's a smart kid.
Think about it.

674
01:10:17,346 --> 01:10:19,580
If she's out there,
I'm sure she's with someone

675
01:10:19,582 --> 01:10:23,750
who's taking her
to the goddamn bridge.

676
01:10:23,752 --> 01:10:28,555
Okay? It's her best option.

677
01:10:30,425 --> 01:10:32,292
We gotta go.

678
01:10:32,294 --> 01:10:36,363
- And we gotta go now.
- Okay.

679
01:10:49,844 --> 01:10:54,982
If anyone tries to cross,
shoot without warning.

680
01:10:54,984 --> 01:10:57,751
We've lost contact
with two more patrols,

681
01:10:57,753 --> 01:11:00,320
and another patrol
ran out of gas.

682
01:11:00,322 --> 01:11:02,923
Most of their men
were killed by--

683
01:11:02,925 --> 01:11:05,726
Shut down every grid,
Lieutenant.

684
01:11:05,728 --> 01:11:06,994
Code 227.

685
01:11:06,996 --> 01:11:10,497
Nobody can leave the town.
Put the planes on alert.

686
01:11:10,499 --> 01:11:12,766
We'll strike
at first sunlight.

687
01:11:12,768 --> 01:11:17,871
But this code was used last
during the Second World War.

688
01:11:17,873 --> 01:11:19,306
Sorry?

689
01:11:19,308 --> 01:11:21,608
Yes, sir!

690
01:11:38,026 --> 01:11:39,693
We need backup.

691
01:11:39,695 --> 01:11:43,330
I repeat, we need backup!

692
01:11:44,832 --> 01:11:46,400
Down, Miriam.

693
01:11:46,402 --> 01:11:47,668
Shh! Okay.

694
01:11:47,670 --> 01:11:50,737
Miriam, we're gonna play
a little game, all right?

695
01:11:50,739 --> 01:11:51,605
What game?

696
01:11:51,607 --> 01:11:55,842
I need you to close your eyes
and count to ten real slow.

697
01:11:55,844 --> 01:11:57,978
- Okay? Can you do that for me.
- Yeah, okay.

698
01:11:57,980 --> 01:12:00,714
Whatever you do,
whatever you hear,

699
01:12:00,716 --> 01:12:04,718
no matter what,
don't peek, okay?

700
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:06,887
Go.

701
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:10,057
One...

702
01:12:10,059 --> 01:12:12,426
two...

703
01:12:12,428 --> 01:12:14,428
three...

704
01:12:18,366 --> 01:12:20,667
four...

705
01:12:34,015 --> 01:12:37,117
Please...
I have two small kids.

706
01:12:37,119 --> 01:12:39,986
But you're fine with
shooting and burning

707
01:12:39,988 --> 01:12:42,956
other people's children, right?

708
01:12:42,958 --> 01:12:46,126
Here's your privilege.

709
01:12:46,128 --> 01:12:47,060
Die human.

710
01:12:47,062 --> 01:12:50,397
- [gunshot]
- ...ten.

711
01:12:52,667 --> 01:12:53,934
Good job, sweetie.

712
01:12:53,936 --> 01:12:57,437
Good job.
Come on, let's go.

713
01:13:12,787 --> 01:13:16,056
- What's your name?
- Alex, sir.

714
01:13:16,058 --> 01:13:18,158
Take us to the bridge
and live, Alex.

715
01:13:18,160 --> 01:13:20,026
Watch your head, Miriam.

716
01:13:20,028 --> 01:13:23,163
- Got her?
- Yup.

717
01:13:30,838 --> 01:13:35,041
Drive! Move this thing.

718
01:13:40,548 --> 01:13:42,549
Relax, Alex.
I'm American special forces.

719
01:13:42,551 --> 01:13:44,918
I need you to take the girl
and me to the bridge.

720
01:13:44,920 --> 01:13:47,821
- Can you do that?
- Of course.

721
01:13:47,823 --> 01:13:49,823
But we are running out of gas.

722
01:13:49,825 --> 01:13:51,825
We can drive less than a mile.

723
01:13:51,827 --> 01:13:56,496
We have to go
to a gas station.

724
01:13:56,498 --> 01:13:59,566
Well, find one.

725
01:14:00,134 --> 01:14:03,904
You cold, sweetie?

726
01:14:06,908 --> 01:14:11,678
There you go. All right. Shh.
Don't think about it.

727
01:14:11,680 --> 01:14:13,046
Back to sleep.

728
01:14:13,048 --> 01:14:15,649
Shh.

729
01:14:23,724 --> 01:14:25,692
- Harold?
- Yeah.

730
01:14:25,694 --> 01:14:27,994
We need to take some water.

731
01:14:27,996 --> 01:14:32,098
Then we've gotta
carry on moving.

732
01:14:38,973 --> 01:14:43,610
I'm gonna go through the door
on the right.

733
01:14:44,846 --> 01:14:45,745
Clear.

734
01:14:45,747 --> 01:14:48,715
All right, I'll cover you.

735
01:14:52,053 --> 01:14:53,920
[gate rattles]

736
01:14:53,922 --> 01:14:56,089
Locked.

737
01:15:10,905 --> 01:15:13,507
[laughs]

738
01:15:13,509 --> 01:15:15,976
Come on.

739
01:15:23,050 --> 01:15:24,885
Thank you, God!

740
01:15:24,887 --> 01:15:27,854
Can you get us
close to the pump?

741
01:15:27,856 --> 01:15:31,591
Uh, no, this is it.

742
01:15:33,594 --> 01:15:36,162
All right.

743
01:15:36,164 --> 01:15:39,232
Miriam, wait here.

744
01:16:04,659 --> 01:16:05,859
You're kidding me.
It's too short.

745
01:16:05,861 --> 01:16:10,664
Go inside. Find something
to put gas in it.

746
01:16:29,584 --> 01:16:31,651
Drop it.

747
01:16:31,953 --> 01:16:34,220
Don't even think to shout.

748
01:16:34,222 --> 01:16:36,189
Move.

749
01:16:36,757 --> 01:16:38,258
Move!

750
01:16:45,132 --> 01:16:49,102
Put down your weapon!
Now! Do it!

751
01:16:50,705 --> 01:16:53,340
Don't make me ask you again!

752
01:16:54,976 --> 01:16:58,078
Mommy? Mommy!

753
01:16:58,813 --> 01:17:02,148
- Dr. Bennett?
- Miriam?

754
01:17:02,984 --> 01:17:03,683
Mommy!

755
01:17:03,685 --> 01:17:06,052
- Thank you. Thank you so much!
- Mommy!

756
01:17:06,054 --> 01:17:09,122
- John saved me.
- Good to see you again, John.

757
01:17:09,124 --> 01:17:10,624
Harold, get in there!

758
01:17:10,626 --> 01:17:12,258
Find something
to put this gas in now!

759
01:17:12,260 --> 01:17:14,728
Double time! Move it!

760
01:17:14,730 --> 01:17:17,864
- Mommy!
- My sweet peanut!

761
01:17:17,866 --> 01:17:19,099
- Oh, baby!
- Mommy!

762
01:17:19,101 --> 01:17:22,068
I thought I'd lost you.

763
01:17:22,070 --> 01:17:26,206
Thank you so much
for saving her.

764
01:17:30,911 --> 01:17:33,213
Let's go! Come on!

765
01:17:33,381 --> 01:17:35,682
You two, come on!

766
01:17:39,820 --> 01:17:41,855
Come on, guys, hurry up!

767
01:17:41,857 --> 01:17:44,991
Let's go, move!

768
01:17:46,027 --> 01:17:48,962
One in the warehouse.
I'll go and get it.

769
01:17:48,964 --> 01:17:49,763
Make it quick.

770
01:17:49,765 --> 01:17:53,299
- I'm on it.
- Hurry up.

771
01:17:58,005 --> 01:18:00,040
Harold, come on!

772
01:18:02,076 --> 01:18:03,376
[growling]

773
01:18:03,378 --> 01:18:05,011
Get down!

774
01:18:05,013 --> 01:18:07,180
[growling]

775
01:18:31,972 --> 01:18:35,075
John?

776
01:18:38,879 --> 01:18:41,181
John?

777
01:18:45,086 --> 01:18:46,720
Go on.

778
01:18:46,722 --> 01:18:48,455
Get out of here.
Go without me. I'm done.

779
01:18:48,457 --> 01:18:51,991
Alex, get them out of here!

780
01:18:52,927 --> 01:18:55,195
- John?
- You need to go.

781
01:18:55,197 --> 01:18:57,497
- Let me see!
- No!

782
01:18:57,499 --> 01:18:58,965
Stay up there.
It's too late.

783
01:18:58,967 --> 01:19:01,468
- Come with us!
- No, I can't, sweetie.

784
